Let's now calculate the present value for the first year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$4,700,000}{\left(1 +  0.0492\right)^{1}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$4,700,000}{1.0492}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$4,479,604}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our calculation, the present value of the salary for the first year is $4,479,604.

Next, let's now calculate the present value for the second year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$5,100,000}{\left(1 +  0.0492\right)^{2}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$5,100,000}{1.10082064}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$4,632,907}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen in our calculation, the present value of the salary for the second year is $4,632,907.

Following, let's calculate the present value for the third year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$5,700,000}{\left(1 +  0.0492\right)^{3}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$5,700,000}{1.154981015}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$4,935,146}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the present value of the salary for the third year is $4,935,146.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the fourth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$6,400,000}{\left(1 +  0.0492\right)^{4}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$6,400,000}{1.211806081}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$5,281,373}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the present value for the fourth year is $5,281,373.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the fifth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$7,100,000}{\left(1 +  0.0492\right)^{5}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$7,100,000}{1.271426941}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$5,584,277}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen in our calculation, the present value of the salary for the fifth year is $5,584,277.

Last, let's calculate the present value for the sixth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$7,800,000}{\left(1 +  0.0492\right)^{6}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$7,800,000}{1.333981146}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$5,847,159}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the present value of the salary in the sixth year is $5,847,159.

Next, since the athlete requested a contract value increase of $2,000,000, we will add the increase to the net present value of the salaries to determine the total net present value of salaries including the increase. Our computation can be expressed in the following equation:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Total NPV } &=\text{NPV of Salaries}+\text{Contract Value Increase}
\end{aligned}$$

Next, calculate the amount for periodic equal quarterly payment distribution.
We will subtract the $10,000,000 signing bonus on the net present value of the arrangement as the signing bonus can be immediately withdrawn. Hence we will use the following formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{NPV for Quarterly payments} &=\text{NPV of Salaries}+\text{Contract Value Increase}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our previous calculation, the effective annual rate is 4.92%; therefore, we will divide the annual rate over the four quarters in a year to determine the effective quarterly rate. We will consider the following formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Quarterly Rate} &=\dfrac{EAR}{4}
\end{aligned}$$

Let's now calculate the effective quarterly rate.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Quarterly Rate} &=\dfrac{0.0492 }{4}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{1.23\%}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen in our calculation, the effective quarterly rate is 1.23%.
